  <refnamediv>
    <refname>imnorm</refname>
    <refpurpose>Normalize input 2-D Image to the range of 0-1 for double, or 0-255 for uint8</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>


<refsynopsisdiv>
   <title>Syntax</title>
   <synopsis>
   y = imnorm(x)
   
   </synopsis>
</refsynopsisdiv>

<refsection>
   <title>Parameters</title>
   <variablelist>
   <varlistentry><term>x :</term>
      <listitem><para> Input 2-D matrix</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   <varlistentry><term>y :</term>
      <listitem><para> Normalized output matrix</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   </variablelist>
</refsection>

<refsection>
   <title>Description</title>
   <para>
This function is used to normalized the 2-D matrix to the range of 0-1, or 0-255 for uint8,
to ensure the 2-D matrix follows the image representation standard in double or uint8 format.
   </para>
   <para>
</para>
</refsection>

